headline: Tariff Decision Doesn't Give FedEx and UPS a Bump on Small Packages
summary: Shippers FedEx and United Parcel Service won’t get a bump from the Supreme Court declaring most of President Trump’s tariffs illegal.  There is a silver lining, though.  A prior de minimis exemption allowed imported goods valued below $800 to enter the country without incurring duties or formal customs procedures.
